{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug: an NPC is stuck in a static T- or A-pose; its legs don’t animate and the character therefore glides / floats up stairs and across the ground.

Generated report: Ashley Williams is seen "floating and moving through the environment in an unrealistic manner," including floating up stairs and passing through a doorway. It attributes this to an animation / physics problem.

Key shared symptoms:
• Character floats / slides instead of walking.
• Occurs when going up stairs / through environment.
• Implies animation not playing correctly.

Missing details in generated report (T-pose, leg movement) do not contradict anything it states—they are simply omitted. The core issue (improper animation causes floating movement) is the same, so the two descriptions refer to the same underlying bug.","match":true}

The generated report concerns the character appearing to float while being lowered from a helicopter because the rope connection is invisible or missing. It does not mention rotor blades or the helicopter’s ability to fly; instead it focuses on character-rope attachment. Therefore the two descriptions point to different issues.","match":false}

The generated report describes a problem where the helicopter’s rotor blades appear stationary or are not rotating as expected. Since they point to the same core issue (non-moving rotor blades on a flying helicopter), the reports refer to the same underlying bug.","match":true}
